  "prompt": "How do I avoid an awkward situation after a break up?",
  "response": "Navigating the aftermath of a breakup can indeed be challenging. Here are some tips to help you avoid awkward situations:\n\n1. **Clear Communication**: Ensure that both parties understand the reasons for the breakup and agree on the boundaries moving forward. This helps avoid misunderstandings.\n\n2. **Respect Boundaries**: Respect the space and privacy of your ex-partner. Avoid reaching out unnecessarily, especially in the immediate aftermath.\n\n3. **Social Media Etiquette**: Consider unfollowing or muting your ex on social media to avoid seeing updates that might make you uncomfortable.\n\n4. **Mutual Friends**: Inform mutual friends about the breakup and ask them to respect your need for space. This can help prevent awkward encounters and conversations.\n\n5. **Avoid Common Hangouts**: If possible, avoid frequenting places where you know your ex might be. This minimizes the chances of running into them unexpectedly.\n\n6. **Be Polite but Brief**: If you do happen to encounter your ex, be polite but keep the interaction brief. A simple \u201chello\u201d or nod can suffice without delving into deeper conversation.\n\n7. **Focus on Yourself**: Engage in activities that make you feel good and help you move forward. This can include hobbies, fitness, or spending time with supportive friends and family.\n\n8. **Seek Support**: If needed, talk to a counselor or therapist to help process your emotions and gain perspective on how to handle post-breakup situations.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s natural to feel awkward initially, but with time and self-care, things will get easier.",
